    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe output from `nvim_echo` loses its first line when run in a scheduled job (e.g., with `timer_start`) when `&cmdheight=0`\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```\r\nset cmdheight=0\r\ncall timer_start(0, { _ -> nvim_echo([[\"foo\\nbar\"]], 0, {}) })\r\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI expect the output to be:\r\n```\r\nfoo\r\nbar\r\nPress ENTER or type command to continue\r\n```\r\nbut it is instead\r\n```\r\n\r\nbar\r\nPress ENTER or type command to continue\r\n```\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.9.0-dev-1312+g908494889\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nRocky Linux 8.6\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nxfce4-terminal 1.0.4\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "This seems to fix the problem:\r\n```diff\r\ndiff --git a/src/nvim/message.c b/src/nvim/message.c\r\nindex b43bc6ce9..73a97d6f7 100644\r\n--- a/src/nvim/message.c\r\n+++ b/src/nvim/message.c\r\n@@ -2365,6 +2365,9 @@ bool msg_do_throttle(void)\r\n void msg_scroll_up(bool may_throttle, bool zerocmd)\r\n {\r\n   if (may_throttle && msg_do_throttle()) {\r\n+    if (!msg_grid.throttled && p_ch == 0) {\r\n+      msg_scrolled_at_flush = msg_scrolled;\r\n+    }\r\n     msg_grid.throttled = true;\r\n   }\r\n   msg_did_scroll = true;\r\n```\r\n\r\nAlthough it looks a bit strange.",
